# Paint Calculator 
# This program reads the width and height of a wall (in meters),
# calculates its area, and the amount of paint needed to cover it.
# Each liter of paint covers 2 square meters.

# User input
width = float(input('Width of the wall (meters)'))
height = float(input('Height of the wall (meters)'))

# Area calculation 
area = width * height

# Paint calculation 
paint_needed = area / 2  
# 1 liter covers 2 m²

# Display results 
print(f'The wall has dimensions {width}x{height} and an area of {area:.2f} m²
print(f'Paint needed: {paint_needed:.2f} liters 
